definition: as far as the eye can see
to put/to place/to release/to free/to let go/to let out/to set off (fireworks)
eye/small hole/crux (of a matter)/CL:隻|只[zhi1],雙|双[shuang1]/classifier for big hollow things (wells, stoves, pots etc)
full moon/to hope/to expect/to visit/to gaze (into the distance)/to look towards/towards

to go/to go to (a place)/(of a time etc) last/just passed/to send/to remove/to get rid of/to reduce/to be apart from in space or time/to die (euphemism)/to play (a part)/(when used either before or after a verb) to go in order to do sth/(after a verb of motion indicates movement away from the speaker)/(used after certain verbs to indicate detachment or separation)

sentences.english: Cozy rooms look out over the district.
sentences.chinese: 放眼望去，都是舒適的房間。

sentences.english: Look closely, a horizontal rail in front of me.
sentences.chinese: 放眼望去，一條條鐵路縱橫在我眼前。

sentences.english: The natural landscape in this region is generally marshy and well watered.
sentences.chinese: 放眼望去，這片區域是沼澤而富水豐沃的。

sentences.english: Dragonstone was still visible above the grasslands.
sentences.chinese: 從草原上放眼望去，龍石山依然看得見。

sentences.english: Standing on the field side, everywhere we look, bumper harvests.
sentences.chinese: 站在田野邊，放眼望去，到處是豐收的景象。

sentences.english: At this time looking into the sky, in my heart you flow rainbow will bloom.
sentences.chinese: 此時放眼望去，天空的流虹便將會在心底油然綻放。

sentences.english: Looking ahead, the whole chicken in a mess, shocking.
sentences.chinese: 放眼望去，整個雞場狼藉一片，觸目驚心。

sentences.english: There were no visible guards or other appurtenances of power.
sentences.chinese: 放眼望去也不見警衛或其它權力標屬。

sentences.english: Looking ahead, like the whole seabed is a three-dimensional map of the world.
sentences.chinese: 放眼望去，整個海底活像是一幅立體的世界地圖。
